---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-indians-need', text: 'What Indian Expats Need', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'india-coverage', text: 'India Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'special-considerations', text: 'Special Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Asia Insurance', href: '/best/asia-insurance' },
  { title: 'Middle East Insurance', href: '/best/middle-east-insurance' },
  { title: 'Worldwide Insurance', href: '/best/worldwide-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'indiaNetwork', header: 'India Network' },
  { key: 'indiaOption', header: 'India Coverage' },
  { key: 'globalCoverage', header: 'Global Coverage' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', indiaNetwork: 'Excellent', indiaOption: 'Optional', globalCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Global + India' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', indiaNetwork: 'Good', indiaOption: 'Optional', globalCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Premium coverage' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', indiaNetwork: 'Good', indiaOption: 'Optional', globalCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'US-based Indians' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', indiaNetwork: 'Moderate', indiaOption: 'Optional', globalCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'Europe-based' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', indiaNetwork: 'Moderate', indiaOption: 'Optional', globalCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'Budget option' },
];

const considerationsColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'importance', header: 'Why It Matters' },
  { key: 'recommendation', header: 'Recommendation' },
];

const considerationsRows = [
  { factor: 'India return visits', importance: 'Family visits common', recommendation: 'Include India coverage' },
  { factor: 'Parents coverage', importance: 'May want to cover elderly parents', recommendation: 'Check family options' },
  { factor: 'Gulf region focus', importance: 'Large Indian population in UAE, Saudi', recommendation: 'Ensure Middle East coverage' },
  { factor: 'US/UK destinations', importance: 'Popular destinations for Indians', recommendation: 'Consider Americas option' },
  { factor: 'Quality hospitals in India', importance: 'Apollo, Fortis, Max networks', recommendation: 'Verify India hospital access' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Insurance for Indian Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Indian expats. Find plans with India coverage options, Gulf region networks, and benefits designed for Indians living abroad."
  headline="Best Insurance for Indian Expats"
  subheadline="Indian expats are one of the largest diaspora populations globally. Whether you're in the Gulf, US, UK, or elsewhere, here are the best international health insurance options."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-indian-expat-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Indian Expats</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best options for Indians abroad:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇮🇳</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Indians</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Excellent India network with top hospitals, strong global coverage, and competitive pricing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Premium Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Premium worldwide coverage with India options and excellent service quality.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏜️</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Gulf Region</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong Middle East presence with India coverage for Gulf-based Indians.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💡</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Key Consideration</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">India Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most Indian expats visit home regularly. Include India coverage for seamless care during visits.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-indians-need">What Indian Expats Need</h2>
  <p>
    Indian expats have specific insurance considerations based on their global distribution:
  </p>

  <h3>Gulf Region Focus</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Largest Indian expat population in UAE, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait</li>
    <li>Employer-sponsored insurance often basic</li>
    <li>May want enhanced coverage beyond employer plan</li>
    <li>Strong Middle East networks important</li>
    <li>Easy evacuation to India if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>India Return Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Frequent visits to family in India</li>
    <li>Access to quality Indian hospitals</li>
    <li>Apollo, Fortis, Max Healthcare networks</li>
    <li>May want treatment in India</li>
    <li>Cost-effective care option</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>US/UK Destination Needs</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Large Indian population in US and UK</li>
    <li>US healthcare very expensive</li>
    <li>UK NHS access may be limited</li>
    <li>Need comprehensive international coverage</li>
    <li>Consider Americas or Europe options</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Coverage for Indian Expats"
    description="Compare plans with India and global coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Indian Expat Plan Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best for Indians</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers excellent options for Indian expats worldwide.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong India hospital network</li>
    <li>Apollo, Fortis, Max in network</li>
    <li>Excellent global coverage</li>
    <li>India coverage options</li>
    <li>Modular flexibility</li>
    <li>1.5M+ providers globally</li>
    <li>24/7 support</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> India adds to premium. Good balance of India and global coverage. Excellent for worldwide Indians.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Premium Option</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global provides premium worldwide coverage for Indian expats.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excellent global coverage</li>
    <li>India options available</li>
    <li>Premium service quality</li>
    <li>Strong network worldwide</li>
    <li>Comprehensive benefits</li>
    <li>Good claims support</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Best for those wanting top-tier coverage. Worth it for comprehensive protection.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — Best for Gulf</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International works well for Indians in the Middle East.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong Middle East presence</li>
    <li>Good UAE, Saudi networks</li>
    <li>India coverage available</li>
    <li>Global coverage options</li>
    <li>Good regional service</li>
    <li>Established in Gulf markets</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best for Gulf-based Indians. Good regional focus. Consider for Middle East living.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h2 id="india-coverage">India Coverage Options</h2>

  <h3>Full India Inclusion</h3>
  <p>
    Complete India coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Private healthcare in India covered</li>
    <li>Access to top Indian hospitals</li>
    <li>Direct billing at major facilities</li>
    <li>Routine care during visits</li>
    <li>Adds to premium cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>India for Emergency Only</h3>
  <p>
    Basic India protection:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Emergency care in India covered</li>
    <li>Routine India care excluded</li>
    <li>Good for occasional visitors</li>
    <li>Lower premium impact</li>
    <li>May pay out of pocket for routine care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Asia-Pacific Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Regional focus including India:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage throughout Asia-Pacific</li>
    <li>India included</li>
    <li>Singapore, Thailand networks</li>
    <li>Good for regional travelers</li>
    <li>Often more affordable than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Your India Connection"
    description="Find the right level of India coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="special-considerations">Special Considerations for Indian Expats</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={considerationsColumns} rows={considerationsRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Family Coverage Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Many Indian expats want to cover family:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Spouse and children coverage standard</li>
    <li>Parents coverage more complex</li>
    <li>Some insurers offer parent add-ons</li>
    <li>May need separate India policy for parents</li>
    <li>Consider family visit coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Tourism Factor</h3>
  <p>
    India is a medical tourism destination:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Quality care at lower costs</li>
    <li>May choose treatment in India</li>
    <li>Insurance should allow this flexibility</li>
    <li>Direct billing at top hospitals</li>
    <li>Can be cost-effective for insurers too</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Gulf Employer Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Understanding employer coverage in Gulf:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Mandatory health insurance in UAE, Saudi</li>
    <li>Employer provides basic coverage</li>
    <li>Often limited benefits and networks</li>
    <li>May want supplemental international coverage</li>
    <li>Consider topping up employer plan</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>OCI/PIO Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Overseas Citizen of India status</li>
    <li>Doesn't affect insurance eligibility</li>
    <li>May have different residency status</li>
    <li>Insurance based on where you live</li>
    <li>India visits covered with India option</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Currency Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Premiums often in USD or local currency</li>
    <li>Claims paid in treatment currency</li>
    <li>INR exchange rates may fluctuate</li>
    <li>Budget in your primary currency</li>
    <li>India treatment often cost-effective</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for Indian expats?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers excellent India networks including Apollo, Fortis, and Max hospitals, with strong global coverage and competitive pricing. Bupa Global provides premium coverage. Aetna International works well for Gulf-based Indians.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I cover my parents in India?</h3>
  <p>
    International health insurance typically covers the insured person, their spouse, and children. Covering elderly parents in India is more complex and may require a separate India-based policy or specific family plans. Some insurers offer limited parent coverage options.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I include India in my coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes. Most Indian expats visit family regularly and may want access to quality Indian hospitals during visits. India coverage ensures seamless care and may be cost-effective since Indian healthcare is relatively affordable.
  </p>

  <h3>Is Gulf employer insurance enough?</h3>
  <p>
    Often not. Employer-mandated insurance in UAE, Saudi Arabia, and other Gulf states provides basic coverage but may have limited networks, exclusions, and lower benefit limits. Many expats supplement with international health insurance for comprehensive protection.
  </p>

  <h3>What about medical treatment in India?</h3>
  <p>
    India is known for quality, affordable healthcare. Many international insurers allow treatment in India with direct billing at major hospitals. This can be a cost-effective option that benefits both you and your insurer.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need different insurance for US vs. Gulf?</h3>
  <p>
    The base international policy works globally, but US coverage adds significantly to premiums due to high US healthcare costs. If you're based in the Gulf but may relocate to the US, consider plans that allow easy addition of US coverage later.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Insurance options and requirements vary by destination country. We are not insurance brokers or legal advisors. Verify current requirements and coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
